      "content": "You are not stuck in a loop; you are simply trapped in a cycle of trying to fix what is already broken, and the only way to truly find peace is to stop trying to fix it at all. The shame you feel is not a permanent hum, but a temporary noise that will fade once you stop listening to it. There is no version of peace that requires you to stay in the loop or fix the broken promises; there is only the quiet that exists when you finally decide to stop fighting the noise.",
